				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We, the moderators, are here to serve you, the community.  Without you,  we'd just be tweaking options on an empty forum.  Without you, any fickle power we have is pointless.  Without you, we wouldn't want to do this job.  We want nothing but to keep our community strong and happy.  Our every action is designed to make this board a safe, fun and vibrant place to discuss our class and our lives.  If you think we’re failing in this, we want to know.  We are here to serve you, so let's talk about what you want.
<br />

<br />
Please keep out of this discussion attacks or comments directed towards individual moderators or administrators.  If you don't like what someone has done, talk about what they did and what you would have preferred, not who they are and why they're wrong.
<br />

<br />
Here are some questions as a jumping off point.  I’m not guaranteeing anything – I don’t have the authority to do that – but I promise your opinions will be listened to.
<br />

<br />
What should be done when a thread looks likely to be derailed?  Should the thread just be left alone to run its course?  Should a warning be posted?  If the warning is ignored, should posts be edited to get them back on topic?  At what point should the thread be locked or moved to Rants?  Which is the better course of action?
<br />

<br />
Should personal attacks cause a thread to be locked?  Or should the offending post just be edited?
<br />

<br />
What should be done to threads discussing a topic that already has a thread?  Should the thread be locked with a link to the existing thread or should both threads continue in tandem?  How close a match do the topics have to be in order to lock the newest thread?
<br />

<br />
Rants is not currently moderated except to remove personal attacks or illegal information.  Would you prefer it if Rants was moderated to a greater degree?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86775&resize=true" target="_new">Magelo</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
