				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">well, personally i'd say the offending posts could be edited out if the whole thread isn't comprised of a flamewar between two people. 
<br />

<br />
when a thread becomes a flamewar between two people and they are the only ones keeping the thread alive, i'd say lock it.  
<br />

<br />
is there an option available to prevent certain users from posting in a thread?  perhaps this is something that could be utilized also if there is such an option, for when people start flaming each other left and right.  it would allow the majority to continue to post onto the thread constructively and keep the flamers out... 
<br />

<br />
perhaps even a 12 hour ban on posting if there was some way to let the ban run out automaticly - doubt this is an option though. - on people who are engaging in a flamewar.
<br />

<br />
locking the thread should be a last resort used only in  totally degenerated threads in my opinion.
<br />

<br />

<br />
as far as locking duplicate threads, i'd say just let the thread with the most action continue on and  lock the other witha  link to the new thread.  there should be a close match though between the threads.  for instance a thread about a specific change shouldn't be referred back to a thread on a general group of changes.    say i wanted to make a post about the specific change to burning sand yesterday, but not talk about all the other patch message stuff.  this is something that in my opinion shouldn't be locked.  but 2 threads on the patch in general should.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99608" target="_blank" class="postlink">Daetien Beyazid</a> 
