				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There have been some very good posts destroyed by a couple people who jump in later to start flaming each other back and forth until the thread gets locked.
<br />

<br />
Frankly I'd rather see those people get their posts deleted, a warning sent to them, and a 1-day ban if they continue.  Let the thread under discussion stay alive, but without the flames.
<br />

<br />
By rule, we are not to re-open a new discussion if the thread was locked.  But that isn't always fair to the people who posted ligitamate, insightful posts on the thread and want to continue the discussion, but without "those people" who caused the thread to be locked. 
<br />

<br />
Anyone who gets a ban can still read posts as Anon, but not reply.
<br />

<br />
Speaking of replies, I'd like to remove the 'quote' key from select people.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing out Loud" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
You know, the ones who quote entire pages of text from somebody, then put a 2 line comment underneath?  
<br />

<br />
Or people who quote entire messages of somebody who already quoted another message, and so on, giving you this pages of quotes within quotes within quotes each time? 
