			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some quick advice from me, no demands though, I have an enormous amount of trust and faith in the crew running these boards.
<br />

<br />
First off, recognize that any action or inaction that you choose to take in a post, <span style="font-style: italic">will</span> piss off someone. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />  
<br />

<br />
Secondly, I'd prefer that you keep as many options open for yourselves as possible. There are times when locking is appropriate, there are times when editing is appropriate, its difficult to write a blueprint for when each tactic should be used.
<br />

<br />
Thirdly, Do your best to try and judge a post on its individual merits. When you're trying to decide whether or not to ban someone, look at the sum of their activity. If you're trying to moderate a discussion, try to focus on what someone says or does within that thread only.
<br />

<br />
Last of all, I think we're just going through a bad period. We're not getting the attention from SOE that we need, and people have started to turn on each other (Casual vs. Uber, Still playing vs. No longer playing, etc.).  These issues have popped up from time to time in the past, but never before with this magnitude. This will pass with time.<br />_________________<br />Naladini
<br />
<a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/player.vm?characterId=103141102" target="_blank" class="postlink">Summoner</a> of 15 Seasons, Najena Server
