			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Locking should be your last resort, not your first.
<br />

<br />
You should only lock a thread when YOU, the moderator, has failed to do you job.  Before locking you have the options of editing certain posts, deleting them, warning individuals, or banning/suspending individuals.  Until all of those options are exhausted, the thread should remain open.
<br />

<br />
Obviously, there are exceptions, such as a flame war between only two people, or spam, etc.<br />_________________<br />Altanis Blazewielder
<br />
Fallen Magician
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Retired</span>
<br />
<img src="http://home.mchsi.com/~bullers4/wsb/media/49602/site1005.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
