				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First and formost, there should be a forum in which personal attacks are allowed. Perhaps make it a passworded forum that requires you to get permission to enter before you can, so that trolls cannot randomly attack individuals, and so that people who simply don't want to read the forum won't be tempted. Call it Flames, make it seperate from rants.
<br />

<br />
Secondly, I agree that locking a post should be a last resort. Edit offending posts, if there are too many to edit or the only reason to leave the thread open would be to continue with personal attacks, ect (in a non Flames forum), then lock the thread.
<br />

<br />
Moderators should explain why they do things. There is a rule about questioning moderator authority, but I can count several times when threads have been locked with no apparent reason, no explination left, and when someone asks why , they get warned.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
