				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have no problem with the moderation on these boards. Its a welcome place to visit compared to the awful crap you have to sift through on the boards with no moderation.
<br />

<br />
For those who complain about some sort of restriction to free speech, here's a thought for you. Why don't you learn to communicate like a normal human being instead of a garbage spewing assclown. And thats about as close to a general flame as I get.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
All the above taken in, I would say the following. Warnings are preferable to banning, editing to locking, moving to deleting. It might take a bit more work on the moderators behalf, but I think giving folks as much benefit of the doubt as possible is a good thing.
<br />

