			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The moderation on these boards has been about right.
<br />

<br />
Disagreements are part of normal civilized communication, and of course differing points of view should all be presentable, on all relevant subjects. Even respectful discussion of moderator decisions should be permissable. However, in the end, we cannot have anarchy and continue to provide a friendly and open community to all; some people must run things, for the benefit of the entire magician community, not just for those who wish to have the "right" to be disrespectful to others.
<br />

<br />
So many internet message boards have campaigns for "anti-censorship" which causes them to become free-for-alls where the lowest common denominator of vulgarity and constant personal attacks are the norm. These boards are then taken over by such, and the vast majority of 'normal' folks stop using them.
<br />

<br />
This board is far above that mire, let it remain so please.
<br />

<br />
If there are a few who want the "freedom" to not be constrained by civilized behaviour, let them form their own community, not ruin ours!
<br />

<br />
Suzanna.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
