				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I will add this,  Unless you know that there is no means for a person to have multiple accounts, then ......
<br />

<br />
The one thing I have seen is this and it can be illustrated by a thread that was locked.  The thread was in regards to Ronald Reagan.  Many people were posting condolences.  One person in particular wanted to rant.  A moderator locked the thread because of the actions of that one.
<br />

<br />
The issue I raise is this, with multiple accounts (assumption) there is the possibility for a single person to get a thread locked by flaming between 2 or more of their accounts.  That appears to me to be a means of posters being allowed to become moderators on threads they don't like.<br />_________________<br />What is your goal, to be right or to understand.
<br />

<br />
You want to attack the person?  Then go ahead and jump into that cesspool, but don't expect me to follow.
<br />

