			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've gotten into heated discussions many times on these boards.  Nearly every time, it's because somebody replied attacking me or insulting an idea, or by making some half informed reply that had nearly nothing to do with what I said in the first place.
<br />

<br />
A huge part of me wishes more people would post with comments like "well, not that I agree or disagree with what he said originally, but your reply has nothing to do with what he actually said" would make me feel a ton better.  I try to make a post describing how our pets DPS needs to be upgraded, and I point out that Epic pet DPS potential is higher then nearly everything else we have.  I get replies of "You won't get Epic 2.0, so just stop asking."  I never asked for Epic 2.0, I reply "I never asked for Epic 2.0, here's what I was saying..."  Then I get more replies that obviously did not read and understand what I was saying and BAM!   The thread is derailed into a war.
<br />

<br />
If more people would put in the effort to read and understand what others were ACTUALLY saying, they would not need to make so many posts.  Threads would not get derailed as often, and we would not post at each other without actually reading and thinking about what the others said.
<br />

<br />
I don't know if there's anything moderators can do about that, other then perhaps step in and say "please keep in mind, the thread was about X, and the original poster never stated what you are disagreeing with..."  /shrug.
<br />

<br />
I make a post stating Epic pet does more DPS then ASoS focused pets.  I get called an idiot, I get flamed for saying that.  They never get stopped from insulting me by moderators.  Parses are done, I'm proved right by the parses.  How long am I gonna put up with getting flamed by people that #1. didn't understand the original point, #2. Don't make an attempt to read and understand what's replied to.  #3. are not putting in the same effort I am to test and verify what's being said?
<br />

<br />
I do in game tests, verify my results, post full math supporting what I was saying, yet I'm the jerk when I flame back somebody who's been riding me the whole way?  What a bunch of crap!  
<br />

<br />
If somebody walks up and punches me in the gut in real life, I'm gonna hit them back.  If somebody chooses not to just disagree with my post, but insult and flame me, they are damn well gonna get it back!  I've tried just ignoring them, and nothing happens.  They don't get checked by a moderator, the thread just turns into a flame war.
<br />

<br />
I think posters on these boards also need to separate facts from opinions better.  If I state "a conjuration mage has a more efficient fire DD, far more efficient magic DD, and far more efficient pet heals, pets, summoned items, CoTH, and mez then an Evocationist, and NO loss for potential DPS."  That is a FACT.  Just the same as "An Evocationist is more effiecient WHILE dealing max DPS then a Conjurationist" is a FACT.  An opinion would be "a conjuration mage is more well rounded then an evocationist."  That's an opinion.
<br />

<br />
I state facts in some of my posts, but then others reply to me as if it's all just opinion, and they make assumptions on what I have said.  They start stating "quotes" from me that I never said or never would say.  Hell yes that pisses me off.  Why is it ok for posters to slander each other by totally distorting what they actually said?
<br />

<br />
In recent threads, this has been what irritated me more then anything.  It's not that people disagreed with me, thats perfectly ok.  It starts good discussions.  It's not that people have different playstyles, thats perfectly ok also.  What irritated me is that they didn't give me the same respect I gave them to read what I wrote and understand it before replying and flaming/disagreeing with something I never said.  Or they try to make general statements like "you just don't accept other people's playstyles" which I NEVER do if you actually read my replies.
<br />

<br />
I'm sure I could be less angry when I post, but then again, everybody has a limit right?  I feel like I've been pushed over my limit on these boards.  I have felt like if threads were being moderated, or other posters kept the thread on topic or worked harder at making sure others were not totally mis-communicating, there would not have been any reason to get angry.
<br />

<br />
I don't know, that's my feeling on the whole thing.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eandori (Retired)</a>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13760" target="_blank" class="postlink">"The pinnacle of pet offensive power can be achieved at level 50 with the epic pet. Does this make sense?"</a></span>
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
