And my pet peeve is not about people arguing and flaming, it's about rule #8 and the fact that the Moderators always seem to have some smart ass comment to post before locking a thread. 
<br />

<br />
There is a reason why there are 2 serverwide channels. Maybe we need 2 MBs.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">Let's stay on topic neither one of those posts were suggestive just critical/observational. I like the ideas I'm seeing so far. Edit first, lock last and if all other means fail. Yes I do know it takes some work however you can get help I am sure. Also in cases of edit, leave your own lil mod note in red. Moving should be done after it's usefulness has been exploited and lastly, we could use a "Gloves off" forum. One where you can rant and PA to some degree. Not full on PAs but minor attacks.
<br />

